bsidiaries owned by the&nbsp;corporation,\nincluding Teshmont, Manitoba Hydro International and Manitoba Hydro Telecom;\nand ","index":"00653","speaker":""},{"html":"����� (t)�� failed to\noffer a plan to actually use the telecommunication assets of Manitoba Hydro to\nbring broadband to rural and northern Manitoba, instead pushing for these\nassets to be sold off; and ","index":"00654","speaker":""},{"html":"����� (u)� failed\nagain to listen to Manitoba producers who have overwhelmingly said that their\napproach to leasing Crown lands will cause irreparable harm to farm families in\nManitoba that are already dealing with serious challenges due to climate\nchange, while also failing to provide them with insurance supports during a\ntime of need; and ","index":"00655","speaker":""},{"html":"����� (v)� continued\nto underspend highways infra�structure by hundreds of millions of dollars,\nwhile also continuing to pursue the selling off and privatization of\ninfrastructure services; and ","index":"00656","speaker":""},{"html":"����� (w) cut\nsupports for French language services at the Universit� de Saint-Boniface,\nSant� en Fran�ais and translation services, and eliminated the assistant deputy\nminister for the Bureau de l'�ducation fran�aise; and ","index":"00657","speaker":""},{"html":"����� (x)� failed to\nmeaningfully consult with Indigenous leaderships for another year regarding the\nLake St.&nbsp;Martin outlet channel and other initiatives that affect\nIndigenous rights, and refused to properly recognize the legitimate rights and\nroles of Indigenous leadership on matters of&nbsp;harvesting and management of\nresources; and","index":"00658","speaker":""},{"html":"����� (y)� failed to\nimplement a living wage, offered no supports for health and safety in\nworkplaces, and are pushing ahead with a defence of a wage-freeze law that was\nruled to be unconstitutional; and","index":"00659","speaker":""},{"html":"����� (z)� ignored\nthe needs of the northern communities who have lost hundreds of mining jobs by\nthe failure to release any funds devoted to supporting mining commu�nities; and","index":"00660","speaker":""},{"html":"����� (aa) failed to\ntake any meaningful action on climate change by continuing to pursue a wasteful\nchallenge to the federal govern�ment's carbon tax, cutting support to local\nenvironmental groups, investing in programs for green jobs or actually make\nprogress on important projects like upgrades to the North End Sewage Treatment\nPlant; and","index":"00661","speaker":""},{"html":"����� (bb) failed to\noffer any supports to new�comers in the province, especially those newcomer\nworkers who work in agri�cultural and manufacturing sectors every day.","index":"00662","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>*</b>\n(16:40) ","index":"00663","speaker":""},{"html":"����� As a consequence of these and many other failings, the 'provin'\ngovernment has thereby lost the trust and confidence of the people of Manitoba\nand this House.","index":"00664","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Is it\nthe pleasure of the House to adopt the amendment? ","index":"00665","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some Honourable Members:</b> Yes.","index":"00666","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some\nHonourable Members:</b> No. ","index":"00667","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Voice Vote</b>","index":"00668","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> All those in favour of the amendment, please say yea.","index":"00669","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some\nHonourable Members:</b> Yea.","index":"00670","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> All those opposed, please say nay.","index":"00671","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some\nHonourable Members:</b> Nay.","index":"00672","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> In my opinion, the Nays have it. ","index":"00673","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Recorded Vote</b>","index":"00674","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Ms.\nNahanni Fontaine (Official Opposition House Leader):</b> Madam Speaker, a\nrecorded vote, please.","index":"00675","speaker":"Nahanni Fontaine"},{"html":"<b>Madam Speaker: </b>A recorded vote having been called, call in the\nmembers.","index":"00676","speaker":""},{"html":"����� For the information of all members, for virtual sittings of the\nHouse, we are required to conduct votes in a different manner than during\nnormal sittings of the House. For members in the House, the vote will be\nconducted in a manner similar to our previous practice. For this part of the\nvote, those in favour will stand to be counted first, followed by those\nagainst. I&nbsp;will note for members that we have modified this system in one\nrespect: once the page states the name of the member standing to be counted,\nthe Clerk will acknowledge that the member has voted by repeating the member's\nname rather than saying Aye.","index":"00677","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Once the count\nin the House is complete, we will conduct an alphabetical roll call of members\nparticipating virtually. For this part of the process, the page will call each\nremote member's name alphabetically and then each remote member must audibly\nstate their vote responding clearly with either I vote yes or I vote no. The\nClerk will then respond to the member's name, followed by yes or no.","index":"00678","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Finally, after\nthe bells stop ringing for any vote, the moderator and the table will need to\ntake a moment to verify that all members listed as remote are actually present\non screen and in their seats and are therefore eligible to vote. ","index":"00679","speaker":""},{"html":"����� This delay\nshould be brief but is necessary to confirm who can vote because for remote\nmembers, being seated before the camera is the equivalent of members being in\ntheir assigned seats in the Chamber when the bells stop ringing.","index":"00680","speaker":""},{"html":"����� The question\nbefore the House is the motion of the honourable Leader of the Official\nOpposition (Mr.&nbsp;Kinew) that is, the amendment to the motion for an address\nin reply to the Speech from the Throne.","index":"00681","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Division</b>","index":"00682","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><i>A RECORDED VOTE </i></b><i>was\ntaken, the result being as follows:</i>","index":"00683","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Yeas</b>","index":"00684","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>Adams, Altomare, Asagwara, Brar,\nBushie, Fontaine, Gerard, Kinew, Lamont, Lamoureux, Lathlin, Lindsey, Maloway,\nMarcelino, Moses, Naylor, Sala, Sandhu, Smith (Point Douglas), Wasyliw,</i> <i>Wiebe\n</i><br>\n<br>\n","index":"00685","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Nays</b>","index":"00686","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>Cox, Cullen, Eichler, Ewasko,\nFielding, Friesen, Goertzen, Gordon, Guenter, Guillemard, Helwer, Isleifson,\nJohnson (Interlake-Gimli), Johnston (Assiniboia), Lagass�, Lagimodiere, Martin,\nMichaleski, Micklefield, Morley-Lecomte, Nesbitt, Pallister, Pedersen, Piwniuk,\nReyes, Schuler, Smith (Lagimodiere), Squires, Stefanson, Teitsma, Wharton,\nWowchuk</i>","index":"00687","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Clerk (Ms. Patricia Chaychuk):</b>\nYeas 21, Nays 32. ","index":"00688","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>*</b> (16:50)","index":"00689","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam Chairperson: </b>I declare the\nsubamendment lost. ","index":"00690","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>* * *</b>","index":"00691","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> The question now before the House is the motion of the honourable\nmember for Swan River (Mr. Wowchuk); that is the motion for an address in reply\nto the Speech from the Throne.","index":"00692","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Do\nmembers wish to have the motion read? ","index":"00693","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some\nHonourable Members:</b> No. ","index":"00694","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> Is it the pleasure of the House to adopt the motion? ","index":"00695","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some\nHonourable Members:</b> Yes. ","index":"00696","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>An\nHonourable Member:</b> No. ","index":"00697","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> I hear a no. ","index":"00698","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Voice Vote</b>","index":"00699","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> All those in favour of the motion, please say yea. ","index":"00700","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some\nHonourable Members:</b> Yea. ","index":"00701","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> All those opposed, please say nay. ","index":"00702","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Some\nHonourable Members:</b> Nay. ","index":"00703","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> In my opinion, the Nay�the Yeas have it. <i>[interjection]</i> ","index":"00704","speaker":""},{"html":"����� You\ndidn't let me finish.","index":"00705","speaker":""},{"html":"����� In my\nopinion, the Yeas have it. ","index":"00706","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Recorded Vote</b>","index":"00707","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Ms.\nNahanni Fontaine (Official Opposition House Leader):</b> Recorded vote, please.\n","index":"00708","speaker":"Nahanni Fontaine"},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> A recorded vote having been called, call in the members. ","index":"00709","speaker":""},{"html":"����� The\nquestion before the House is the motion of&nbsp;the honourable member for Swan\nRiver, that is the motion for an address in reply to the Speech from the\nThrone. ","index":"00710","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Division</b>","index":"00711","speaker":""},{"html":"<b><i>A\nRECORDED VOTE </i></b><i>was taken, the result being as follows:</i>","index":"00712","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Yeas</b>","index":"00713","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>Cox,\nCullen, Eichler, Ewasko, Fielding, Friesen, Goertzen, Gordon, Guenter,\nGuillemard, Helwer, Isleifson, Johnson (Interlake-Gimli), Johnston\n(Assiniboia), Lagass�, Lagimodiere, Martin, Michaleski, Micklefield, Morley‑Lecomte,\nNesbitt, Pallister, Pedersen, Piwniuk, Reyes, Schuler, Smith (Lagimodi�re),\nSmook, Squires, Stefanson, Teitsma, Wharton, Wowchuk.</i>","index":"00714","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Nays</b>","index":"00715","speaker":""},{"html":"<i>Adams,\nAltomare, Asagwara, Brar, Bushie, Fontaine, Gerrard, Kinew, Lamont, Lamoureux,\nLathlin, Lindsey, Maloway, Marcelino, Moses, Naylor, Sala, Sandhu, Smith\n(Point&nbsp;Douglas), Wasyliw, Wiebe.</i>","index":"00716","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Clerk:</b>\nYeas 33, Nays 21.","index":"00717","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> I declare the motion carried. ","index":"00718","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>*\n* *</b>","index":"00719","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam Speaker:</b> And at this time I\nwould just like to thank everybody. This was history being made right now in\nManitoba with the first virtual remote vote by a number of our members. And so\nthank you to everybody in the House for helping make this happen, and to everybody\nthat showed up remotely, this was the part of virtual that worried us the most,\nand I have to commend our team here, our clerks and everybody helping them. ","index":"00720","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>*</b>\n(17:00)","index":"00721","speaker":""},{"html":"����� What�the\namount of work that went into making sure the rules around this were in place\nand that this would work took a lot of time, and I do want to say to them a\nvery, very special thank-you because this was a little bit scary for all of us.\n","index":"00722","speaker":""},{"html":"And to the pages who are in a brand new world here with having to call\nthe vote as they did, you did a great job. ","index":"00723","speaker":""},{"html":"����� And,\nwith the hour being 5 p.m., this House is adjourned and stands adjourned until\n1:30 p.m. tomorrow. ","index":"00724","speaker":""}]}